City holds press conference on POTUS, conference traffic
The City and County of Honolulu will hold a press conference at 2:30 p.m. to discuss what will be a busy week on Oahu roads.
Click here to watch the press conference via live stream.
President Barack Obama is scheduled to arrive Wednesday evening, and closures will be in effect while he is in town.
Additional closures have already been set for the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) World Conservation Congress, which begins Thursday at the Hawaii Convention Center and Neal S. Blaisdell Center.
